  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2008-03-10",
    "date": "2008-04-08T15:47:58Z",
    "text": "Helping Communities Act of 2008 - Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to make grants to states for providing foreclosure-mitigation counseling to homeowners of owner-occupied single family homes with mortgage loans in default or in danger of default.\n\n\n\nRequires each state recipient to provide at least 95% of the grant amounts to nonprofit entities.\n\nAuthorizes additional FY2008 appropriations for community development block grant assistance under the Housing and Community Development Act of 1974."
